noun.name: zebra
noun.discription: a striped African mammal related to horses and donkeys

object1.name: giraffe
object1.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a tall African mammal with a long neck and legs

object2.name: elephant
object2.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large African mammal with a long trunk and tusks

object3.name: kangaroo
object3.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large Australian marsupial that hops

object4.name: penguin
object4.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a flightless bird found in the Southern Hemisphere

object5.name: rhinoceros
object5.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large, thick-skinned mammal with one or two horns on its snout

object6.name: hippopotamus
object6.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large, semi-aquatic mammal native to Africa

object7.name: crocodile
object7.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large, predatory reptile with a long snout and powerful jaws

object8.name: ostrich
object8.discription: in parallel with 'zebra', is a large, flightless bird native to Africa
